-- German Tax on Extending Nuclear Plants May Be 50%, Bild Zeitung Reports
-- Oliver Suess
-- 2010-07-17T08:09:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-17/german-tax-on-extending-nuclear-plants-may-be-50-bild-zeitung-reports.html

          
          
             Germany may impose levies of at
least 50 percent on profits companies generate from extending
the life of nuclear power reactors,  Bild Zeitung  reported,
citing German Economy Minister  Rainer Bruederle .  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
